Package org.apache.sis.util

Class UnsupportedImplementationException

  • Object
    • Throwable
      • Exception
        • RuntimeException
          • UnsupportedOperationException
            • UnsupportedImplementationException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    public class UnsupportedImplementationException
extends UnsupportedOperationException
    Thrown when an operation can not use arbitrary implementation of an interface, and a given instance does not met the requirement. For example this exception may be thrown when an operation requires an Apache SIS implementation of a GeoAPI interface.
    Since:
    0.3
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    Defined in the sis-utility module
